  '9d3d9744-be99-415b-9221-34ac3be9b60c',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Scala sbt — Lock Files, Version Pinning, and Dependency Auditing$escape$,
  $escape$sbt has no built-in lock file — you need the `sbt-dependency-lock` plugin. Once added to `project/plugins.sbt`, run `sbt dependencyLockWrite` to generate `build.sbt.lock`, a reproducible snapshot of your full resolved dependency graph. Commit this file. In CI, `sbt dependencyLockCheck` fails the build if live resolution diverges from the lock — catching silent upgrades when upstream artifacts are republished to the same version coordinate.

Always pin exact versions in `build.sbt` (e.g., `"2.10.0"`, not `"2.+"`). Dynamic ranges like `latest.release` bypass lock semantics entirely — Ivy resolves them at build time, making builds non-reproducible. Use `%%` (double percent) to automatically append the Scala binary version suffix (`_3`, `_2.13`); this is mandatory for cross-compiled libraries.

For upgrade tracking, `sbt-updates` exposes `sbt dependencyUpdates`, listing newer coordinates against Maven Central. For CVE auditing, the OWASP `sbt-dependency-check` plugin queries the NVD database: `sbt dependencyCheck` generates an HTML report flagging known vulnerabilities across your full transitive graph — not just direct dependencies.

Commit `build.sbt.lock`, ban dynamic version ranges, and gate every PR on `dependencyLockCheck`.$escape$,
  $escape$// project/plugins.sbt
addSbtPlugin("software.purpledragon" % "sbt-dependency-lock"  % "1.4.1")
addSbtPlugin("com.timushev.sbt"      % "sbt-updates"          % "0.6.4")
addSbtPlugin("org.owasp"             % "sbt-dependency-check" % "9.0.7")

// build.sbt — pin exact versions; never use dynamic ranges
libraryDependencies ++= Seq(
  "org.typelevel" %% "cats-core" % "2.10.0",
  "co.fs2"        %% "fs2-core"  % "3.10.0",
  "org.http4s"    %% "http4s-dsl"% "0.23.27"
)

// sbt dependencyLockWrite   → generate/update build.sbt.lock
// sbt dependencyLockCheck   → CI gate: fails on drift
// sbt dependencyUpdates     → list available upstream upgrades
// sbt dependencyCheck       → OWASP NVD CVE report$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
